The swap modules confirm a concrete asymmetry: `swap` charges fees even when it consumes point orders, but `addLimOrder(..., currentPoint, ...)` can consume the same resting opposite orders without any fee path. I’m checking whether that asymmetry can be dismissed as explicit protocol intent or whether it is strong enough to keep as an economic finding.
